# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# idle-less configuration
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Or run the installer which generates .env automatically:
#   bash install.sh
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Domain Configuration
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Each domain uses the pattern DOMAIN_{i}_* where {i} is 1, 2, 3...
# You can configure as many domains as needed.

# === Domain 1 (primary) ===
DOMAIN_1_HOSTNAME=chat.example.com
DOMAIN_1_IP=192.168.1.22
DOMAIN_1_PORT=3080
DOMAIN_1_USE_HTTPS=no
DOMAIN_1_USE_SSL=yes

# Host directory containing cert files for this domain.
# Mounted into the container as /etc/certificate_provider/live/chat.example.com/
DOMAIN_1_CERTS_HOST_PATH=/etc/letsencrypt/live/chat.example.com

# === Domain 2 (additional — uncomment to enable) ===
#DOMAIN_2_HOSTNAME=app.example.com
#DOMAIN_2_IP=192.168.1.50
#DOMAIN_2_PORT=8080
#DOMAIN_2_USE_HTTPS=no
#DOMAIN_2_USE_SSL=yes
#DOMAIN_2_CERTS_HOST_PATH=/etc/letsencrypt/live/app.example.com

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SSL Certificates — How It Works
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Each domain has its own DOMAIN_{i}_CERTS_HOST_PATH pointing to
# the directory on your host where the cert files live.
# That directory is mounted into the container as /etc/certificate_provider/live/<hostname>/.
#
# The container expects fullchain.pem and privkey.pem inside the
# mounted directory. Just point DOMAIN_{i}_CERTS_HOST_PATH to the
# host directory that contains them.
#
# Example — Let's Encrypt:
#
#   DOMAIN_1_CERTS_HOST_PATH=/etc/letsencrypt/live/chat.example.com
#
#   Host:       /etc/letsencrypt/live/chat.example.com/fullchain.pem
#                ↓ mounted as ↓
#   Container:  /etc/certificate_provider/live/chat.example.com/fullchain.pem
#
# Each domain can point to a different directory:
#   DOMAIN_1_CERTS_HOST_PATH=/etc/letsencrypt/live/chat.example.com
#   DOMAIN_2_CERTS_HOST_PATH=/home/user/ssl/app-certs
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Wakeforce (install with: bash install.sh --wakeforce)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only needed when running with --wakeforce flag.
# Adds Wake-on-LAN gateway per domain.
#
#LICENSE_KEY=your-license-key-here
#DOMAIN_1_CONFIG=backend
#DOMAIN_1_MAC=D8:9E:F3:12:D0:10
#DOMAIN_1_BROADCAST=192.168.1.255
#DOMAIN_1_LAN=eth0
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Wakeforce Standalone (install with: bash install.sh --wakeforce-only)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Runs wakeforce without the reverse-proxy. Each domain gets a
# direct port mapping starting at 8182 (domain 1 → 8182, domain 2 → 8183, ...).
#
# Required variables per domain:
#   DOMAIN_{i}_HOSTNAME, DOMAIN_{i}_IP, DOMAIN_{i}_PORT
#   DOMAIN_{i}_CONFIG, DOMAIN_{i}_MAC, DOMAIN_{i}_BROADCAST, DOMAIN_{i}_LAN
#   LICENSE_KEY
#
# SSL/HTTPS variables are NOT used in this mode.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Variable Reference
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DOMAIN_{i}_HOSTNAME        — Public hostname (e.g. chat.example.com)
# DOMAIN_{i}_IP              — Backend server IP on your LAN
# DOMAIN_{i}_PORT            — Backend server port
# DOMAIN_{i}_USE_HTTPS       — Backend uses HTTPS? (yes/no, default: no)
# DOMAIN_{i}_USE_SSL         — Enable SSL termination? (yes/no)
# DOMAIN_{i}_CERTS_HOST_PATH — Host dir with fullchain.pem + privkey.pem
#
# Wakeforce only (--wakeforce):
# LICENSE_KEY                — Wakeforce license key
# DOMAIN_{i}_CONFIG          — "default" (proxy only) or "backend" (with Wakeforce)
# DOMAIN_{i}_MAC             — Target machine MAC address (for Wake-on-LAN)
# DOMAIN_{i}_BROADCAST       — LAN broadcast IP (for Wake-on-LAN)
# DOMAIN_{i}_LAN             — Host network interface (for macvlan)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
